<vulnerability_guide>
  <title>ML MODEL POISONING</title>

  <critical>Model poisoning attacks corrupt machine learning models during training to create backdoors, degrade performance on specific inputs, or cause targeted misclassifications. Unlike inference-time attacks, poisoning affects all users of the compromised model and persists until retraining with clean data.</critical>

  <scope>
    - Training data poisoning
    - Model backdoor insertion
    - Federated learning attacks
    - Transfer learning exploitation
    - Supply chain model compromise
    - Fine-tuning vulnerabilities
  </scope>

